         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Court House ¶ Kilmore ¶ Vic. ¶ April 1 1859 ¶ My dear Sir, ¶  ¶ I had yesterday the pleasure to receive your letter of the 30 Ultimo ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ […] ¶ illegible. ¶  ¶ my co-operation in r...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">59.04.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Andrew McCrae</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 13071 Royal Society of Victoria Exploration Committee records, box 2075/5, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Court House</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Kilmore<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">April 1 1859</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I had yesterday the pleasure to receive your letter of the 30 Ultimo<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[…]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">illegible.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>my co-operation in raising a sum of money to supplement a donation of £1000 given by a Colonist for the purpose of carrying out the exploration of the interior.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>what became known as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Burke and Wills Exploring Expedition, 1860-1.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This commission I would willingly undertake, but when I tell you, that in consequence of an application from Dr McAdam — I have already tried the Kilmore people &amp; could raise but £2.15/— which I remitted about a week ago by post-office order to Dr McAdam, but the receipt of which he has not acknowledged.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Documents relating to McCrae's remittance are filed with this letter, as follows:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">(1)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Exploration Fund | Mr McCrae presents his compliments to Dr McAdam &amp; begs to enclose Subscription List for the fund shewing a receipt of One Pound 15/— for which Mr McCrae now begs to enclose a Postoffice order. | Court House | Kilmore | March 23 1859</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">(2)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mr Jamieson, requested to allow the prefixed Subscription List &amp; letter to lie on the counter of the Colonial Bank of Australasia &amp; to call the attention of customers to the same | Andrew McCrae PM [Police Magistrate] | Kilmore | Dec 16 1858</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.493in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">(3)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>printed subscription list<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>headed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'EXPLORATION FUND COMMITTEE. |<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>His Honor Sir William F. Stawell, Chief Justice, Chairman' with,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the bottom,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'This List to be forwarded, with the remittance, to the Hon. Treasurer, Dr.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>WILKIE, Collins Street, Melbourne. |<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>JOHN MACADAM, M.D., Hon. Secretary.' The body oif the form<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>lists the contributors as Andrew McCrae, PM. Kilmore £1; J. P. Jamieson 10 shillings; J. McPherson 5<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>shillings.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[McPherson not positively identified.]</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>You will at once see that another appeal would serve no good purpose — I should mention that the population of Kilmore is not a wealthy one and the many claims have been made upon them for churches schools a hospital a mechanics Institute &amp;c —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Fetes at your fine Gardens — Balls — and Theatrical performances in which you might enlist Mr Coppin seem to me the most likely way of raising a considerable sum of money. &amp;c — […]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">two illegible words.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>besides to have active committees — &amp; the different quarters of the city — Cui bono? was the question always put to me when I asked a subscription — Victoria would not benefit by the discovery of new pastures &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have my hands full here as besides the work of this bench<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>McCrae was appointed Police Magistrate at Kilmore in 1857.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have to visit another 17 miles distant &amp; have wardens work to do at a gold field at about the same distance</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>About the middle of the month I hope to be able to come down to Melbourne when then I promise myself pleasure in renewal of our intimacy — I need hardly tell you that I have been a highly gratified observer of the rapid progress you have been making in the world of science &amp; also the good opinion of the most worthy of this Colony. —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Believe me always my dear friend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Andrew McCrae</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Ferd. Müeller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
